            h1 How it works
          section.vertical-slide
            h1 HTML5 Custom elements (through a polyfill)
            p.fragment Allow you to write HTML-like syntax for 3D objects on the web.
            p.fragment
              | Use stadard DOM selection APIs -- document.querySelector, setAttribute, even jQuery -- to manipulate 3D objects!
          section.vertical-slide
            h1 A layer of abstraction over three.js
            p.fragment  A-Frame's HTML-like syntax makes it a breeze to build.
            p.fragment Use attributes to set values like rotation, position and scale easily.
            pre.
              \n                                  
          section.vertical-slide
            h1 Everything kept in memory
            p Writing to the DOM is slow, but JavaScript can be pretty zippy. 
            p.fragment
